   <body>
      <context>
         <hazardstatement type="danger">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>Perform a total power off of the UPS system before connecting
the battery cables to the battery breaker.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <hazardstatement type="danger">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>Hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>For TT and TN systems each stand alone cabinet of the
system must be individually connected to the protective earthing terminal
in the distribution board that supplies the system.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <hazardstatement type="warning">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>Hazard of arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>Use M8 bolts and nuts to connect the power cables.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the left side panel from the main battery cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Main Battery Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/gupxcab600iec_removecoverleftside_w120mm_0000151251.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Install the control terminal block kit in the dedicated
location in the main battery cabinet with the six supplied screws.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Main Battery Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/gupxcab600iec_installterminalkit_w120mm_0000151250.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Lockout/Tagout the battery breaker in the battery breaker
box.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the four bolts on the protection cover and remove
the protection cover.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Main Battery Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/gupxcab600iec_terminalremoveprotectioncover_w120mm_0000151249.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the PE cable through the bottom of the main battery
cabinet and connect to the PE busbar.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Main Battery Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/gupxpcab600iec_connectpe_w120mm_0000152211.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the battery cables (+,-) from the battery breaker
box through the bottom of the battery cabinet and connect to the battery
breaker busbars (+,-).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Main Battery Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/gupxcab600iec_terminalconnectupsbatcables_w120mm_0000152209.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>If adjacent battery cabinets are present: Interconnect
the batteries through the sides of the battery cabinets.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the battery cables (+,-) from the batteries to
the battery busbars in the rear of the control terminal block kit.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Side View of the Main Battery Cabinet Seen from the Left</title>
                  <image href="../Images/gupxcab600-800iec_connectbatcablesinside_w120mm_0000152912.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig>
                  <title>Battery Wiring Diagram – One Battery Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/0s-9660_-_Reality_pxc_iec_cablingdiagrambatterytype_xp12v1800-1_cabinet_w120mm_0000162699.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Battery Wiring Diagram – Two Battery Cabinets</title>
                  <image href="../Images/0s-9660_-_Reality_pxc_iec_cablingdiagrambatterytype_xp12v1800-2_cabinets_w170mm_0000162698.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Battery Wiring Diagram – Three Battery Cabinets</title>
                  <image href="../Images/0s-9660_-_Reality_pxc_iec_cablingdiagrambatterytype_xp12v1800-3_cabinets_w170mm_0000162697.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the protection cover with the four bolts.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the left side panel on the main battery cabinet.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
